data.name: richTextBox12.Text
data.value:
There can be seen path of the animation in the editor with colored main axes. Number of dots corresponds to number of frames. One red dot indicates starting point of the animation.
From path is directly derived viewing direction of the camera. Each new frame has camera's normal computed as direction from path point to the centre of the animation.

data.name: richTextBox7.Text
data.value:
Launches animation process from first selected animation at Scene window. If no animation is checked, no animation process can be executed.
New window will be shown with partial rendering results and remaining time. Progress changes image by image.
Only one animation process may be executed at the same time.
After animation is completed, total time is displayed.
Animation will be automatically saved to selected file which path is displayed at bottom of the window.
Animation can be cancelled.

data.name: richTextBox5.Text
data.value:
Total Time: rendering time
Recursion: depth of recursion
Is Antialiasing (YES/NO) : if antialiasing was activated
Optimization: NONE: optimization disabled RTREE: STR packing algorithm for bounding volumes OCTREE: octree optimization for bounding volumes KDTREE: first type of kd-tree with bounding volumes around centers of objects KDTREE_POINTS: kd-tree with bounding volumes formed by border points of objects
Size: resotution of image
Total Objects: total number of objects in the scene
Object Tests: number of tests of intersections with ray and object
BV Tests: number of tests of intersections with ray and bounding volumes of objects. (Visible only for enabled optimization)

data.name: richTextBox4.Text
data.value:
Launches drawing process from the only one selected image at Scene window.
New window will be shown with partial rendering results.
More than one drawing process may be executed at the same time.
After drawing is completed, total time is displayed and image menu will be enabled.
Image can be saved in several formats (PNG, JPEG. BMP, other).
Each drawing window has its own About box available displaying details about rendering.

data.name: richTextBox9.Text
data.value:
On picture above we can see custom object transformed in the board by user. This transformation can be done by selecting proper triangle of custom object and then after right click on one of three vertices dragging mouse to any direction. This can be done only with custom object.
Point in the center of the object reffers to its center in Properties window of the object. This center is used to simlify computation of direction of all triangles normals. Thus any normal has its direction away from the center.

data.name: richTextBox8.Text
data.value:
On image we can see many objects: sphere, cone and cylinder, which overlap, so popup menu was shown where currently selected is sphere indicated with bolder line.
There is also visible plane with its normal (short line in one corner of plane).
Other object is camera with black direction vector and orange its up direction. Other lines and ellipse is for better illustration of camera angles.
Two circles (white and yellow) represents lights.
On the image are also visible axes which may be enabled in board menu.

data.name: richTextBox6.Text
data.value:
Board displays objects in editor. Objects can be selected, translated, rotated or modified (color change).
Board is in many ways interacive. It responses on user activities. Most of them are done by mouse:
WHEEL UP/DOWN: zooms editor LEFT CLICK: selects object if is located at mouse position. If more objects are located at the same mouse position, popup menu will be shown with those objects. Each item in menu sonsist of its image and label. Holding mouse left button while moving mouse rotates whole editor. RIGHT CLICK: One single right click just selects some object. If object is selected, holding right click above it and draging mouse will move object in editor. If no object is selected and right mouse button is pressed while mouse is moving, whole editor will be shifted too. LEFT DOUBLE CLICK: deselects object and shows active image in Properties window

data.name: richTextBox11.Text
data.value:
Properties window is main tool to modifying all objects.
It always displays currently selected item from Scene window. All changes to that object will be visited at Board immediately. If no object is selected, active image will be shown in the window.
Each item has its own properties.

data.name: richTextBox1.Text
data.value:
Adds new scene to the current scene. It means, that new scene loaded from the file will be added to the current scene.
If loaded scene contains objects with the same label as old objects, new object will be uniquely relabeled.
After file opening new form will be shown where object selecting is required. Checked object means that it will be added to the current scene. Checked camera means it will replace current camera.

data.name: richTextBox2.Text
data.value:
Loads saved scene and replaces the current scene.
Current scene will be lost.
Saved scene is in XML format. It can also be modified by extern editor with valid values. If invalid values during loading appear, then will be replaced by initial values.

data.name: richTextBox10.Text
data.value:
In scene window are shown all objects in the current scene together with available images and animations.
Items are shown in list. Checked item means activated object in editor and visible at rendered image.
Only one image can be activated at the same time. But any animation can be checked at the same time and for animation process will be used first checked animation in the list.
From the Scene menu: objects can be added to the scene, or selected items can be removed.
